snippet.textDisplay:
i'm enjoying this comeback a lot because it's loona and i've waiting for 1 year for them.
that said, my 'problem' with 'so what' is: it seems to be heavily inspired on boygroups? i know that bgs are a thing and that they're more popular over the world cofcofbts and that's exactly what makes me unconfortable: i don't really like how bgs sounds/dress.
i don't mean that a girlgroup needs to be cute or feminine, i'm all here for strong ggs - but like in snsd's 'the boys' or 'you think' and not just like mimicking boygroups.
some part of it says: a girlgroup can do anything, even boygroups' concept.
other says: a girlgroup's concept can't be as strong and popular as a boygroup's one.


for me, twice's 'fancy' is still the best song of 2019. i don't really like how loona keeps doing dance covers of boygroups instead of celebrating the work of feminine groups in kpop. idk if it's just me but it gives me the wrong feeling.

snippet.textDisplay:
just something to add. at 1:43, you can see yeojin wearing a school girl outfit that is blue, reminiscent of the one jinsoul wore in SCL. yeojins representative color is orange and jinsouls is blue which are complimentary colors. maybe this is to further connect them? anyway im just rambling. this song is so good, pls keep on streaming!

edit: OK SO I HAVE A THEORY. so butterfly ended with gowon going back in time right? (idrk the details of this storyline if someone could catch me up id appreciate it) well this mv could be an interpretation of an alternative loonaverse storyline.

theres a big representation of kim lip and jinsoul in this mv. (kim lip in cathedral, red fire, jinsouls color blue being referenced in yeojin hyunjin and choerry) in the loonaverse theology overview, its said that kim lip and jinsoul bear fruits of knowledge and life. perhaps their fruits are spreading which is why we see a diversity of women.

choerry and hyunjin stay together in this timeline, partaking in the influence of kim lip and jinsoul (the clothes they wear say blue is my color) (they probably partook in jinsouls fruit) choerry doesn’t have any purple representation on her because kim lip and jinsoul possibly do not blend their colors in this timeline. and hyunjin is choerry’s mirror, so she stays with her (the new lipsoul of this timeline)

we don’t see vivi much because in this timeline, she was not killed. olivia was never abandoned, so vivi never even meets yves. in fact, i don’t think vivi even meets jinsoul.

none of the girls are with their colors. over representation of just blue, red, and black. did heejin never create colors for the girls? which is why jinsoul is still on the train, yyxy still in eden, choerry at the train station waiting (hyunjin has to be there too, mirror), haseul never kills her alternative self, yeojin is still lost. theyre exploring the back of the moon they built in hi high. but on this side, their colors aren’t well mixed. now kim lip and jinsouls fruits are spreading everywhere, which were the things that cause yyxy to rebel and for hi high to happen. they’re causing chaos. and those colors they used to have helped regulate the loonaverse. heejin lost control, but doesn’t notice. what are colors anyway, when the back of moon is lived in red, black, and blue?

yeojin is eventually influenced by jinsouls fruit. (represented by jinsouls school uniform and her hair) since she and haseul go together and she was lost, haseul is lost too. also, yeojins orange being represented by its opposite color blue is a sign that this timeline is opposite to the one we all know. also, the reverse of the damage to the white feather can symbolize that in this timeline, haseul did not kill her alternative self (as seen in let me in)

olivia seems to have spread her chaos in this timeline under the influence of jinsoul(?). (holding fire so that’s confusing, maybe its lip) yves seems to wonder with her as she doesn’t have her other half anymore (vivi) (maybe yves becomes teacher from l4e since she oversees ballet??) gowon and chuu are represented as innocent girls, who are probably taken advantage of by olivia (parallel but not opposite to how they were told to make the bracelet by olivia) in this timeline, olivia uses chuu and gowon to spread chaos and knowledge (kim lips fruit). in the actual timeline, olivia uses them to connect universes and lives (jinsouls fruit).

so basically, so what is the opposite of hi high. but this is all just me speculating. if i got anything wrong or you wanna add something, please reply!

edit 2: did some more thinking. i read a theory that since jinsoul connects to the killing of vivi, maybe vivi doesn’t eat the fruit? another addition is that gowon stops at room 404. 4 is yeojin. maybe gowon knows that something changed with yeojin. also, gowon wears yellow. yellow(hyunjin)+blue(jinsoul)+hye(gray)=gowon. in this universe, she stays yellow. same with chuu but with red. maybe gowon realizes the change in storyline as she was the one who turned back time. and she realizes it through yeojin since yeojins orange and haseuls green have always been connected. but before they got their colors, gowon and chuu were green and orange before they were tinted by olivia. so basically gowon is adjacent to yeojin.

EDIT 3: (no one will see my comment but whatever) just to clear things up, these are the things that are still present.
-hyunjin and choerry were together from the beginning
-yyxy is still in eden
-they still have their representative animals (haseul still is a white bird as seen at the end visual)
